pageContext.claim: “Jobless claims in the United States have reached their lowest (BEST) level in over 50 years!”
pageContext.analysis: Trump is close, but pushes the envelope by saying "more than 50 years." The Labor Department said claims for jobless aid fell to 192,000, the lowest since September 1969. The four-week average, which is less volatile, was the lowest since November 1969.
